<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/115: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-20T18:00:00-04:00">June
                                        20, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1536. For Moose. Please inform King Ibn Saud immediately that, with
                                reference to his message transmitted in Cairo’s 1667, June 17, 11
                                a.m., Landis is being recalled to Washington to discuss the matters
                                to which the King refers and that it is hoped it will be possible
                                promptly to take care of Saudi Arabia’s immediate supply and
                                transport requirements and to work out a satisfactory long-range
                                Saudi Arabian requirements program. Inform Landis.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>